from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split


df = train_df[['question','topic']].dropna()

le = LabelEncoder()
df['label'] = le.fit_transform(df['topic'])
num_classes = len(le.classes_)
print("Topics:", le.classes_, "→", num_classes, "classes")

questions = df['question'].values
labels    = df['label'].values

temp_q, test_q, temp_y, test_y = train_test_split(
    questions, labels, test_size=0.2, stratify=labels, random_state=42)

train_q, valid_q, train_y, valid_y = train_test_split(
    temp_q, temp_y, test_size=0.2, stratify=temp_y, random_state=42)

print("Sizes:", len(train_q), len(valid_q), len(test_q))

import tensorflow as tf

train_tf = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((train_q, train_y))
valid_tf = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((valid_q, valid_y))

train_dataset = train_tf.shuffle(buffer_size=10000).batch(batch_size=64).prefetch(tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
valid_dataset = valid_tf.batch(batch_size=64).prefetch(tf.data.AUTOTUNE)

from tensorflow.keras import Sequential
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.Input(shape=(1,), dtype=tf.string),
    vectorizer,
    tf.keras.layers.Embedding(input_dim=len(vectorizer.get_vocabulary()), output_dim=64, mask_zero=True),
    tf.keras.layers.Bidirectional(tf.keras.layers.LSTM(64)),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')
])
model.compile(
    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
    optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(1e-4),
    metrics=['accuracy']
)
model.summary()
model.fit(train_dataset, epochs=10, validation_data=valid_dataset, validation_steps=20)

valid_loss, valid_acc = model.evaluate(valid_dataset)

print('Validation Loss: {}'.format(valid_loss))
print('Validation Accuracy: ',valid_acc)
